\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid6650702\charrsid6650702 Mary:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid6650702\charrsid11233106 
Well, when I was five, it was regarded as the age at which you had to come home.  Complete fiction, I think.  It\rquote s an amazing }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid14178613\charrsid11233106 idea that}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid6650702\charrsid11233106  the children had to be separated from their mothers.  The mothers had to stay with the fathers, because they couldn\rquote 
t trust them, probably, to stay on their own \endash  a question of fidelity, probably.  But they sent all their children home.  I know lots of others 
who have had this destiny in store for them.  But the hard thing was, I reached five, and because they thought I would be lonely at home with my grandparents, they sent my sister, who was only three.  It was terribly hard for her.  It was all right for me
, there were two of us, and she was there (LAUGHS) to amuse me!  But she\rquote s really suffered so much for it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid6650702\charrsid11233106 Paul:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid6650702\charrsid11233106 
And do you feel that you suffered too, from that separation?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid6650702\charrsid11233106 Mary:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid6650702\charrsid11233106 
I never did until very recently.  At this age, you look back on your life a
nd you learn more things about people, and I have learnt that it was a very subtle kind of deprivation and neglect that nobody would have known about in those days at all.  I learnt this from a musicologist who was trying to explain to me why I was not mu
sical.  I'm a-musical, in fact.  And I said it couldn\rquote t be hereditary because my parents played and sang, but could it be the effect of being brought up in another country\rquote s tonal system, with different music?  And he said, \'93
No.  Your nannies and local, immediate }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid999000\charrsid11233106 servants}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid6650702\charrsid11233106  probably didn\rquote t have the courage to sing in their own native little lullaby homely tunes, so you never got the background of regular music of their country, and you didn
\rquote t get any background, if your parents weren\rquote t there.  And so you never ever tuned your ears to music at all\'94.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid6650702\charrsid6650702  
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid6650702\charrsid6650702 Paul:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid6650702\charrsid6650702 
Would you say that you were close to your mother or father, then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid6650702\charrsid6650702 Mary:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid6650702\charrsid6650702 We couldn\rquote 
t be!  (LAUGHS)  We were two thousand miles away, or whatever it is!
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid6650702\charrsid6650702 Paul:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid6650702\charrsid6650702 (LAUGHS}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid999000 ) }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid6650702\charrsid6650702 But you had those first years, and then 
did you not see them for holidays?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid6650702\charrsid6650702 Mary:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid6650702\charrsid6650702 
Not very much in the first years either.  I can\rquote t remember them tremendously well in the first years.  I remember my father much better, because when my mother died, he looked after us and brought us up, and then, 
of course, he revived all the memories by talking about it a lot. 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid6650702\charrsid6650702 Paul:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid6650702\charrsid6650702 
