d he wanted to do whatever the economists were doing, as far as he knew it, which was pretty elementary \endash 
 it was about cost-benefit, price, supply and demand in unmonetarised economies.  People did very interesting work on that at that time, but he wasn\rquote t 
in on it, and most of them were on the substantivist side, against him, and I was torn.  I thought we ought to be benefiting from what the economists were doing.
