\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid6650702\charrsid6650702 I liked it, yes.  Yes.  I\rquote d never seen Evans-Pritchard, I\rquote 
d never read a book like it, and I had a kind of pictorial sense of a very powerful abstract painting rather than a fussy detailed thing.  The strong structural lines impressed me enormously, and how he got structure out of the very unpromising means that
 he had in his fingers, [to show how] the organisation of their lives, was always organised by principles, very highly principled, so that you\rquote 
d wonder what they did when they would produce a rule, you know - where the women are the cattle are not, you know
!  (LAUGHS) So I thought he must be very old.  I thought only an old person could get away from the detail so well, and manage to produce an abstract description of what the society was.  I was amazed to find he was in his forties when I met him?  And I t
hink he was the most intellectual of the whole bunch, even more than Meyer Fortes.  Everybody loved him dearly.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-1871\li1871\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin1871\itap0\pararsid6650702 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid6650702\charrsid6650702 
