s a very brilliant book, yes.  Well, they had two different marriage systems going \endash  one before and one afterwards.  But that wasn\rquote 
t happening with us really, people were still trying to marry according to the old traditions, or to make it look as if they were.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid6650702\charrsid6650702 Paul:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid6650702\charrsid6650702 
Anyway, returning to the fieldwork.  So, there you are, you\rquote ve told them that you\rquote re learning the language, so how do you get to observe?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid6650702\charrsid6650702 Mary:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid6650702\charrsid6650702 Oh well, I\rquote 
