\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid6650702\charrsid6650702  from those conversations which meant nothing.  But you had to edit it all up.  Once they came to see me, and said, \'93Come on, you\rquote ve been here for months, and you still don
\rquote t know our language.  Come on.  We\rquote re going to give you a good test\'94.  They brought a little boy in front, \'93What\rquote s that?\'94  \'93Head\'94.  So I said, \'93Inshuit\'94, and \'93
elbow - luo", and I gave the answers to all the words they said, and I was very happy, because I was finally going to learn what their words were for the groin, and the social/sexual organs
.  They were so polite, they never mentioned them.  And I thought I really needed to know that for my grammar.  And so [we] went down the little boy, and we got to his stomach, and we got to his hips, then they went straight to his knees!  So polite, they
