\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid6650702\charrsid6650702 Mary:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid6650702\charrsid6650702 
Yes.  Absolutely.  I told Marco this.  Well, I had a very nice school, I told you about it before, and liked it very much, but I knew it wasn\rquote t very strong.  And I didn\rquote t know anything about Europe, I was very c
onscious of ignorance, and I felt that to go away and do something very exotic and far away, I would never get to know my own home.  And I wanted to do Italy.  I didn\rquote 
t think of doing Greece.  But I felt, as I was born in Italy, it would be a good idea to 
go back and to study a small Italian village.  This is relevant to the History of Anthropology, actually, not to me only, because I got absolutely no encouragement, and I was telling Marco, who\rquote 
s interested in this particular point about academic authority, that they had good reason not to want me to go, because none of them could have supervised.  There wasn\rquote 
t anybody there, in the [Oxford] Department, who could have properly supervised a thesis on Mediterranean areas.  And, moreover, there wasn\rquote t anybody 
there who could have supervised, not just Italy, but any Mediterranean area, except John Christiani was there, and he could have supervised Greece.  Somehow, behind his back, he might have liked us to go to Greece.  I don\rquote 
t think he would have if he knew how bad I am at languages.  But Evans-Pritchard and Fortes ran it, and they said, \'93It has to be Africa.  There\rquote s no theory developed for the Mediterranean\'94
, which meant I would only do some sort of superficial journalistic thing.  Even if I had been supervised, there wasn\rquote 
t anything to say about Greek villages.  And that has remained the plight of Mediterranean Studies, except for Arab Studies, which are Mediterranean, but they count as Arab.  So when Julian Pitt-Rivers, who was younger than I was, and who r
ecently died - I wrote a little commemoration of him in a book we published.  Well, he wanted to go to - where did he go?  Italy?  Yes.
