t find any money for him.  And his mother paid for his research.  Which is going back to the old days, when only people with money, family money, could go into anthropology.  People like Lubbock and Haddon and so on, they\rquote 
d all been supported by their families.  So Julian was quite angry about that, I guess.  And it\rquote s perfectly true, he did suffer, theoretically.  He won\rquote t admit it.  But the only theory t
hat was going was the theory about shame and honour, and they didn\rquote t ever manage to make categories that would stick, so it remains a muddle, complete muddle, about shame.  So I think they were perfectly right to stop me.  I\rquote 
