m glad I remembered the Courgs and about formal rituals, and the relation of rituals to society, it was what he got from Radcliffe-Brown too.  But Max Gluckman was a tremendously powerful person.  He came a year later, so I\rquote d
 got myself ensconced before he came.  And we felt \endash  we, who had been there before \endash  that here was sort of newcomers intruding on our private space.  Max, and John Barnes, [and Clyde Mitchell] who wrote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
