 off and left my child and husband with his mother, and I went back for the long vac.  And I knew that was the end of fieldwork, whereas a real anthropologist has to go on going back to the field.  And also, to extend their field knowledge, they have to g
o round - so that you\rquote re not just a Lele expert, but you\rquote re the Congolese expert, you know.  And there are many other peoples, and you\rquote re implicitly doing comparative work, although it only looks as if you\rquote 
re doing ethnographic, because you\rquote ve got enough tribes with enough held in common, for you to be able to be interested in the variations.  But I obviously couldn\rquote 
t do that kind of career once I had a husband and a first child, a second child and a third child.  So it appeared that I would do the things that were coming to hand.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid6650702\charrsid6650702 Paul:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid6650702\charrsid6650702 
And then there was the trouble in the Congo too.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid6650702\charrsid6650702 Mary:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid6650702\charrsid6650702 Exactly.  I couldn
\rquote t get back to the Congo either, no.  So I couldn\rquote t do anthropology of that kind, of the gathering kind.  And the children had mumps, no, I had mumps o
r something like that, and I began to think about pollution, as a result of thinking about contamination and keeping myself in quarantine from the children, and things like that.  And have written about that.  And so I realised that there was a great deal
 of contamination theory caught up inside these rules about cleanness \endash 
 the contact.  And so I got interested in it that way.  And I particularly thought - even in the field, I sent for a copy of the Bible, and managed to read Leviticus for the first time.  I\rquote 
d never read any part of the Bible directly.  Convent Schools don\rquote t teach Old Testament.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid6650702\charrsid6650702 Paul:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid6650702\charrsid6650702 
