re organising their lives, they need to classify.  They need to classify in order to organise, and so, therefore, you could understand a classification system by looking at the organisation.  But I didn\rquote 
t do that for the sake of these animals that were forbidden for food.  I thought it was enough that they didn\rquote t fit the classification system.  So I let go of my main pillar for organising it, organising my book.
  Now I realise that, thanks to other peo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid986406 ple\rquote s work, particularly Valeri Valerio }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
